						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the well situated behind the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>1634 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in Śaka 1557, Bhāva Kārttika, ba. 15 corresponding to 1634 A.D. (expired), November 10, Monday.</p>						

						<p>It states that certain Rāmānāyuḍu got constructed the wells with the help of the people and restricted to pay the tax on these wells, to the officials, who used to collect the taxes on these wells enormously for drawing the water at Remiḍicherla. Remiḍicherla is situated in Vinikonḍasīma.</p>						

						</summary>
